item.description:
Syntax # svn copy [BRANCH-FROM-URL] [BRANCH-TO-URL] -m &lt;COMMIT-LOG-MESSAGE&gt;
svn copy [^/PATH-TO-BRANCH-FROM] [^/PATH-TO-BRANCH-TO] -m &lt;COMMIT-LOG-MESSAGE&gt;
As you might have noticed, we use svn copy command to create branches, tags and shelves (we&rsquo;ll skip mentioning tags and shelves in the next paragraphs). This is the same command used to copy items in your working copy and into the repository.
svn copy is used for branching because, branch is technically a copy of the source you copy from.
